This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for semantic parsing, which are typically covered in the arXiv sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a Graph Neural Network (GNN) architecture also suggests a potential fit with the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on generating logical forms from text and entities could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
